---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageBanner from '../components/PageBanner.astro';
---

<Layout title="About" description="About Dos Ríos - Argentine Tango and Nuevo in Winnipeg.">
  <PageBanner title="About" />

  <div class="container page-content">
    <div class="prose">
      <h2>Who We Are</h2>
      <p>
        Dos Ríos is a community of Argentine tango dancers based in Winnipeg, Manitoba.
        We embrace both traditional and nuevo styles, and organize milongas, practicas,
        and classes to bring tango to the city - welcoming dancers of all levels.
      </p>

      <h2>The Styles</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>Traditional</strong> - danced to the classic orchestras of the Golden Age:
        D'Arienzo, Pugliese, Di Sarli, Troilo. Close embrace, structured ronda, tandas and cortinas.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Nuevo</strong> - an open, exploratory approach to the dance that draws on
        the same vocabulary but invites more improvisation, open embrace, and contemporary music
        including Piazzolla and electronic tango.
      </p>
      <p>
        Many of our events are mixed - check the style tag on each event listing to know what to expect.
      </p>

      <h2>What We Do</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>Milongas</strong> - social tango dances. Traditional milongas follow ronda
        etiquette with tandas and cortinas; nuevo milongas are more open in format.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Practicas</strong> - open practice sessions where you can work on technique,
        ask questions, and dance informally across both styles.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Classes</strong> - instruction for beginners through to experienced dancers,
        covering technique, musicality, and connection in both traditional and nuevo.
      </p>

      <h2>Get Involved</h2>
      <p>
        The best way to stay connected is to join our
        <a href="/discord" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Discord server</a>
        where we post event announcements, share music, and keep the conversation going between dances.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
.page-content {
  padding-top: 3rem;
  padding-bottom: 5rem;
}
</style>
